<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,822,2035]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Head creamy white with two pale orange to red patches on crown, one on each side of midline. Pronotum yellow with four orange to red patches on disc, area between the patches pale yellow or whitish. Scutum and scutellum yellow. Forewings hyaline mottled with light and dark brown, veins reddish brown, ventral surface of thorax pale stramineous, sometimes marked with dark brown. Legs pale stramineous, abdomen dark brown with lateral edges yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="116" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,822,2035]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis box="[199,365,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
<collectingCountry box="[199,257,1002,1027]" name="Malta" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia
</emphasis>
. Pygofer in lateral view longer than its height, posterior margin broadly rounded, macrosetae confined to posterior half. Valve 
<taxonomicName box="[516,625,1038,1063]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
with posterior angle more broadly rounded, 
<number box="[1122,1157,1039,1063]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="1.7">1.7</number>
times as broad at base as long medially. Subgenital plates elongate 
<taxonomicName box="[658,769,1074,1099]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
, without membranous fingerlike process at apex, setae uniseriate, marginal in addition to hairlike short setae. Style about 
<number box="[895,930,1110,1135]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="3.5">3.5</number>
times as long as wide at base, subapical lobe well developed, apophysis slightly bifid and ventrally directed. Connective Y-shaped with stem approximately 
<number box="[1387,1436,1146,1171]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="0.66">0.66</number>
times as long as total length. Aedeagus with shafts short, cylindrical, dorsally curved, surface with numerous minute denticles, gonopores apical, pair of long narrow closely opposed processes, approximately twice length of shafts arising between bases of shafts, extending posteriorly and curving slightly dorsally, with row of small, teeth along distal half of lateral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,822,2035]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis box="[199,392,1326,1351]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite 
<number box="[598,633,1327,1351]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="1.7">1.7</number>
times as wide at base as medially long, posterior margin convex with median rounded lobe notched in middle. Gonocaxa I with denticles over lateral margins, base of first pair of valvulae abruptly narrowed caudally. Teeth on second pair of valvulae shallow of uniform size, without secondary dentition, ventroapical margin entire.
</paragraph>
